The paper discusses the need for improving the security of data stored in untrusted servers or databases, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes a tool that combines advances in database technologies and cryptographic tools, which suggests that it could also fall under the categories of databases (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper mentions the use of signal processing fundamentals for computation, which could suggest that it falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of security on key signal processing kernels, which could suggest that it falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
